    "_tier_finding": "Flutter ICI is negligible at all spacings >=1 bin (residual-timing-driven wobble is small after pilot tracking). The reverb-ISI FLOOR (~18 dB no-CP, ~21 dB with 5.3ms CP) is the real cap on constellation ORDER: it comfortably clears DQPSK (need 18 dB) but NOT a 6dB-margin 16QAM (need 26 dB) even with a CP. => denser SPACING is cheap; higher ORDER is the expensive axis and needs a CP + the reverb floor lifted (shorter acoustic path / line-in)."
  },
